very sweet if you could come at nine.

287
00:18:09,007 --> 00:18:11,079
And help us with whatever
pops up at the last minute.

288
00:18:14,092 --> 00:18:15,669
I shall be delighted.
- Thank you.

289
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:18,632
But that's not what you
came here to tell me.

290
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:27,542
I did have something else I
wanted to talk to you about.

291
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:28,916
Ah.

292
00:18:29,401 --> 00:18:30,143
Mother.

293
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,091
You and she are being talked about.

294
00:18:33,624 --> 00:18:35,227
Everyone knows but dad.

295
00:18:35,909 --> 00:18:37,239
You've become a town scandal.

296
00:18:42,692 --> 00:18:43,965
It's an idle world, Rachel.

297
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:47,635
Hundreds of people with nothing
to occupy their time except ..

298
00:18:51,676 --> 00:18:53,554
That still isn't what you
came here to tell me.

299
00:18:55,558 --> 00:18:56,375
What is it?

300
00:18:56,972 --> 00:18:58,057
It's you, Jamie.

301
00:18:58,583 --> 00:18:59,541
It is you and I.

302
00:19:00,179 --> 00:19:03,920
It's been nearly four months since
we began seeing a lot of each other.

303
00:19:04,737 --> 00:19:05,463
I know.

304
00:19:05,651 --> 00:19:07,539
I cannot keep on any longer this way.

305
00:19:08,325 --> 00:19:11,020
It's not easy for me, Rachel.
- We've got to stop being furtive.

306
00:19:14,082 --> 00:19:16,179
A strange girl.
- In what way am I strange?

307
00:19:17,012 --> 00:19:18,536
Is it strange to fall in love?

308
00:19:18,899 --> 00:19:20,029
To want what you love?

309
00:19:21,256 --> 00:19:21,985
My dear.

310
00:19:23,129 --> 00:19:24,431
I couldn't let you in for ..

311
00:19:24,978 --> 00:19:26,533
This.
- There's no need for this.

312
00:19:28,271 --> 00:19:29,824
We could get married, you and I.

313
00:19:30,718 --> 00:19:32,614
Why not? I have my own money.

314
00:19:32,989 --> 00:19:35,178
I will come into almost three
million on my next birthday.

315
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:36,218
Oh.

316
00:19:37,172 --> 00:19:39,160
I didn't mean to talk about that.
- That's alright.

317
00:19:40,313 --> 00:19:42,292
You are privileged to talk
about money to me.

318
00:19:43,001 --> 00:19:43,691
Jamie.

319
00:19:44,259 --> 00:19:46,240
Why shouldn't we announce
our engagement tonight?

320
00:19:50,963 --> 00:19:52,382
That's impossible.
- Why?

321
00:20:03,518 --> 00:20:04,227
I see.

322
00:20:05,964 --> 00:20:07,555
Jamie, you've got to break with this.

323
00:20:07,962 --> 00:20:08,577
Hmm.

324
00:20:09,352 --> 00:20:10,482
That is not so simple.

325
00:20:10,787 --> 00:20:12,577
If you loved me as I love you.

326
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:14,339
You would find it very simple.

327
00:20:15,513 --> 00:20:17,892
How do you suppose I feel
when I see you with mother?

328
00:20:18,718 --> 00:20:21,077
How do you suppose I'll feel
tonight at my own party?

329
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:23,664
What do you think it will mean to me ..

330
00:20:23,852 --> 00:20:26,732
When I see you lead the Grand March
with her on Friday night?

331
00:20:32,577 --> 00:20:33,364
Catherine.

332
00:20:33,967 --> 00:20:35,244
And her Potemkin.

333
00:20:40,881 --> 00:20:41,707
Rachel.

334
00:20:46,093 --> 00:20:47,166
You must be patient.

335
00:20:49,332 --> 00:20:50,046
Please.

336
00:20:51,356 --> 00:20:52,675
Kiss me, Jamie.

337
00:21:04,456 --> 00:21:05,414
You must go now.

338
00:21:06,376 --> 00:21:09,523
I suppose I have got to start
learning to obey you sometime.

339
00:21:13,745 --> 00:21:14,474
Goodbye.

340
00:21:17,015 --> 00:21:17,744
Goodbye.

341
00:21:43,069 --> 00:21:44,001
Pardon me, sir.

342
00:21:45,399 --> 00:21:46,615
It is 12 o'clock.

343
00:21:47,980 --> 00:21:49,825
It's what?
It's 12 o'clock, sir.

344
00:21:51,905 --> 00:21:53,075
Miss Fendley's party.

345
00:21:56,568 --> 00:21:57,269
Oh yes.

346
00:22:03,744 --> 00:22:05,303
I can't imagine what happened to him.

347
00:22:05,522 --> 00:22:07,135
What could happen to Jamie Darricott?

348
00:22:07,542 --> 00:22:10,811
If you knew the number of women who try
to trap him into going to their parties.

349
00:22:11,161 --> 00:22:13,603
If you had any idea ..
- It's such a lovely party.

350
00:22:13,894 --> 00:22:15,860
What difference does it
make if he comes or not?

351
00:22:16,048 --> 00:22:17,146
A lot of difference.

352
00:22:17,519 --> 00:22:19,980
It's my party and he might have had
the common courtesy to be here.

353
00:22:20,279 --> 00:22:21,592
Oh, Rachel dear.

354
00:22:22,124 --> 00:22:23,453
What difference does it make?

355
00:22:23,887 --> 00:22:25,675
Whether he's courteous to you or not?

356
00:22:26,256 --> 00:22:28,187
It's time you left Jamie
Darricott alone, mother.

357
00:22:28,735 --> 00:22:30,763
If he's interested in any one Fendley ..
- Rachel.

358
00:22:31,091 --> 00:22:33,326
It's the truth.
You've fooled yourself long enough.

359
00:22:33,725 --> 00:22:36,397
You don't really think Jamie Darricott
is coming here to see you?

360
00:22:36,696 --> 00:22:37,815
Elaine, dear.

361
00:22:38,132 --> 00:22:39,573
It was so lovely.

362
00:22:39,845 --> 00:22:41,500
Therese, you're not going?
- Yes.

363
00:22:41,788 --> 00:22:43,090
We really must, Mrs Fendley.

364
00:22:43,703 --> 00:22:45,725
I hate to, but I'm leaving
for home tomorrow and ..

365
00:22:46,203 --> 00:22:48,284
When I was your age I never
thought of going to bed ..

366
00:22:48,472 --> 00:22:51,364
Until the others thought of getting up.
- I have so much to do tomorrow morning.

367
00:22:51,744 --> 00:22:53,825
Now that you've met us you
must come and see us often.

368
00:22:54,163 --> 00:22:55,035
Thank you.

369
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:58,123
Say goodnight to Mr Fendley for me.
- Yes. Indeed I will.

370
00:23:06,441 --> 00:23:07,166
Gaston.

371
00:23:07,615 --> 00:23:08,695
You had better wait.

372
00:23:09,229 --> 00:23:10,218
I shan't be long.

373
00:23:12,018 --> 00:23:13,359
How do you do, Mrs Blanton.

374
00:23:30,623 --> 00:23:32,457
Aunt Theresa. Who is that man?

375
00:23:33,209 --> 00:23:34,786
Are you trying to be funny, Norma?

376
00:23:35,213 --> 00:23:36,126
No. Who is he?

377
00:23:36,838 --> 00:23:38,094
That is Jamie Darricott.

378
00:23:38,534 --> 00:23:39,887
This year's ladies' man.

379
00:23:41,585 --> 00:23:43,327
Ladies' man?
- Ladies' man.

380
00:23:44,239 --> 00:23:47,210
And at the moment 'the ladies'
happen to be Mrs Fendley.

381
00:23:49,231 --> 00:23:50,590
Goodnight, dear.
- Goodnight.

382
00:23:51,216 --> 00:23:52,088
Yes, Anthony?

383
00:23:52,437 --> 00:23:54,325
Mr James Darricott has just come in.

384
00:23:54,966 --> 00:23:57,179
Jamie? Why, I must ..
- One moment, mother.

385
00:23:58,410 --> 00:24:00,074
If he's to join this party I'm leaving.

386
00:24:01,364 --> 00:24:03,082
You are being a silly boy, Anthony.

387
00:24:03,389 --> 00:24:05,148
I am not silly.
He is cheap and disgusting.

388
00:24:05,336 --> 00:24:06,926
Don't talk like that about a friend.

389
00:24:07,203 --> 00:24:09,100
He's not a friend.
Do you know what they say?

390
00:24:09,381 --> 00:24:10,110
Anthony.

391
00:24:10,461 --> 00:24:12,451
I must forbid you to
speak that way to me.

392
00:24:13,159 --> 00:24:14,003
As you wish.

393
00:24:14,868 --> 00:24:16,361
But if he stays, I go.

394
00:24:17,738 --> 00:24:20,746
You are always to do
whatever suits you, Anthony.

395
00:24:21,730 --> 00:24:23,471
Goodnight, mother.
- Goodnight, dear.

396
00:24:30,175 --> 00:24:30,906
Jamie.

397
00:24:33,049 --> 00:24:33,944
Jamie.

398
00:24:37,493 --> 00:24:38,605
Where have you been?

399
00:24:39,220 --> 00:24:40,350
Where have I not been?

400
00:24:40,912 --> 00:24:42,374
I asked you to be here at nine.

401
00:24:42,818 --> 00:24:43,926
You did, my dear.

402
00:24:44,419 --> 00:24:46,646
Do you I'll put up with
your insults much longer?

403
00:24:47,933 --> 00:24:48,964
How do you do.

404
00:24:49,567 --> 00:24:52,521
Would I be insulting you if I asked you
to be good enough to lower your voice?

405
00:24:52,821 --> 00:24:54,094
You are doing it perfectly.

406
00:24:55,369 --> 00:24:56,756
You are trying to humiliate me.

407
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:58,478
Who is she?

408
00:24:59,562 --> 00:25:00,694
Thank you, no.

409
00:25:10,665 --> 00:25:11,309
Well.

410
00:25:12,670 --> 00:25:13,986
Our dÃ©butante child.

411
00:25:15,086 --> 00:25:16,073
My felicitations.

412
00:25:16,824 --> 00:25:18,857
Thank you. Aren't you just a bit late?

413
00:25:19,286 --> 00:25:20,570
Oh .. a bit.

414
00:25:21,036 --> 00:25:22,595
I've been waiting for you since nine.

415
00:25:22,874 --> 00:25:25,199
If you think I am going to forgive
you, you're badly mistaken.

416
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:28,774
You'll forgive me.

417
00:25:29,632 --> 00:25:30,805
I am afraid I shall.

418
00:25:32,205 --> 00:25:34,450
That's what makes me more
furious than anything else.

419
00:25:39,641 --> 00:25:40,345
Well.

420
00:25:41,579 --> 00:25:42,822
Now for our charming host.

421
00:25:43,010 --> 00:25:45,246
No. You can stay and
talk to me for a moment.

422
00:25:48,683 --> 00:25:50,448
Jamie.
- My dear Elaine.

423
00:25:51,207 --> 00:25:53,254
If you must know, I am sorry I was late.

424
00:25:53,563 --> 00:25:55,860
And you know I didn't
mean anything I said.

425
00:25:57,363 --> 00:25:58,464
I suppose you didn't.

426
00:25:59,886 --> 00:26:00,787
But sometimes.

427
00:26:02,549 --> 00:26:03,409
Sometimes ..

428
00:26:04,693 --> 00:26:05,537
What, Jamie?

429
00:26:09,356 --> 00:26:10,085
Nothing.

430
00:26:11,606 --> 00:26:12,536
Nothing at all.

431
00:26:18,865 --> 00:26:19,709
How are you?

432
00:26:51,422 --> 00:26:52,263
Thank you.

433
00:26:53,747 --> 00:26:54,820
Well, how do you do?

434
00:26:56,627 --> 00:26:57,910
We have met before.

435
00:26:58,904 --> 00:26:59,643
Have we?

436
00:27:00,109 --> 00:27:00,810
Oh yes.

437
00:27:01,218 --> 00:27:04,262
Last night as you were leaving the
Fendleys with Mrs Blanton. Remember?

438
00:27:05,150 --> 00:27:06,114
I see.

439
00:27:06,787 --> 00:27:10,425
Yes. I suppose to a 'ladies' man' that
does constitute an introduction.

440
00:27:12,325 --> 00:27:13,398
Then you do know me.

441
00:27:15,823 --> 00:27:16,477
You.

442
00:27:17,272 --> 00:27:18,831
You don't live here in New York, huh?

443
00:27:19,957 --> 00:27:21,144
What makes you think so?

444
00:27:21,866 --> 00:27:23,168
I think I should have known.

445
00:27:25,561 --> 00:27:27,162
Remaining here for some time?

446
00:27:28,594 --> 00:27:29,695
I am leaving tonight.

447
00:27:29,993 --> 00:27:30,861
For my home.

448
00:27:31,589 --> 00:27:32,266
Why?

449
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:34,845
Surely you don't want to leave New York?

450
00:27:35,615 --> 00:27:36,635
I've got to.

451
00:27:37,136 --> 00:27:37,878
Got to?

452
00:27:39,005 --> 00:27:40,064
That is slave talk.

453
00:27:40,671 --> 00:27:42,287
You ought to be doing what you want to.

454
00:27:42,593 --> 00:27:43,731
While you can want to.

455
00:27:45,288 --> 00:27:46,589
I generally do.

456
00:27:49,413 --> 00:27:51,702
I'm the little man who can
show you all this big city.

457
00:27:53,323 --> 00:27:54,253
Do you know ..

458
00:27:54,548 --> 00:27:56,765
That's one of the few things
that I can take your word for.

459
00:27:59,303 --> 00:28:00,547
But I am taking the train.

460
00:28:02,163 --> 00:28:03,436
Do you know they tell me ..

461
00:28:03,955 --> 00:28:05,886
That they have a train
nearly every day now.

462
00:28:07,484 --> 00:28:09,387
I could show you a lot
of this town in 24 hours.

463
00:28:09,822 --> 00:28:10,551
Somehow.

464
00:28:10,923 --> 00:28:13,295
I think your New York and
my New York are different.

465
00:28:14,251 --> 00:28:15,324
Suppose we find out?

466
00:28:16,002 --> 00:28:17,291
Let's make the grand tour.

467
00:28:17,805 --> 00:28:18,906
See the clock around.

468
00:28:19,670 --> 00:28:21,687
See New York in all its
different lights and shades.

469
00:28:22,016 --> 00:28:23,088
High life. Low life.

470
00:28:23,443 --> 00:28:24,516
Uptown and downtown.

471
00:28:25,834 --> 00:28:26,935
Starting say, with ..

472
00:28:27,407 --> 00:28:29,532
Dinner at the St Regis.
Or The Embassy maybe.

473
00:28:30,115 --> 00:28:32,123
Dance a little.
Drop in a little musical piece.

474
00:28:32,621 --> 00:28:33,957
Catch a night at the opera.

475
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,131
And then a midnight
flight above the city.

476
00:28:36,591 --> 00:28:38,122
We can turn the plane over and over.

477
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:45,151
The town would go round like a
wheel with you sitting on the hub.

478
00:28:46,388 --> 00:28:48,748
You'll never know New York until
you see it as the moon sees it.

479
00:28:49,287 --> 00:28:52,334
Then a nightclub or two.
And out in time to catch the sunrise.

480
00:28:52,659 --> 00:28:53,932
Somewhere along the Hudson.

481
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:56,671
The sun does some of its very
nicest rising around here.

482
00:28:57,672 --> 00:29:00,824
Then we could separate long enough
for a bath and a change of clothes.

483
00:29:01,093 --> 00:29:02,886
You think you can live
without me that long?

484
00:29:03,156 --> 00:29:04,950
After 12 hours of Jamie Darricott.

485
00:29:05,359 --> 00:29:07,560
I doubt if I would be able
to breathe any other air.

486
00:29:08,915 --> 00:29:11,061
And after breakfast we'll
keep on going and going.

487
00:29:11,906 --> 00:29:12,797
And at 7:30.

488
00:29:13,235 --> 00:29:14,537
I deposit you at your train.

489
00:29:15,327 --> 00:29:18,181
I doubt if we would be able to
stand more than a 24-hour stretch.

490
00:29:18,541 --> 00:29:20,413
Perhaps you could stand it for 24 hours.

491
00:29:20,772 --> 00:29:21,702
You are strong.

492
00:29:22,451 --> 00:29:24,399
But I'm just a weak,
defenseless little woman.

493
00:29:24,986 --> 00:29:26,371
Ah. But you could trust me.

494
00:29:27,244 --> 00:29:28,631
Perhaps it's me I am afraid of.

495
00:29:30,573 --> 00:29:31,331
You know.

496
00:29:31,696 --> 00:29:33,327
There is only one slight catch.

497
00:29:34,022 --> 00:29:37,025
I'm meeting my aunt here and she stays
with me until I take the train at 7:30.

498
00:29:37,391 --> 00:29:39,719
Ah, then it's a bargain.
You get rid of your aunt.

499
00:29:40,235 --> 00:29:43,078
Telegraph your people you've been
unavoidably detained for 24 hours.

500
00:29:43,986 --> 00:29:45,601
And at 7:30 I will call for you.

501
00:29:46,019 --> 00:29:46,731
Where?

502
00:29:47,295 --> 00:29:48,597
At the Transylvania Station.

503
00:29:49,405 --> 00:29:50,678
I don't know which track.

504
00:29:51,006 --> 00:29:53,213
I will take you to the train
myself tomorrow night.

505
00:29:54,593 --> 00:29:55,878
When I return to New York.

506
00:29:56,066 --> 00:29:58,169
That is the time for the
Darricott round-the-town tour.

507
00:29:58,396 --> 00:30:00,182
You may never get back
and I may be dead.

508
00:30:00,612 --> 00:30:01,227
You?

509
00:30:01,726 --> 00:30:02,862
You'll live for ever.

510
00:30:03,050 --> 00:30:03,865
I doubt it.

511
00:30:04,195 --> 00:30:06,267
Dying is getting to be quite
a habit around here.

512
00:30:06,774 --> 00:30:08,934
And it's a terrible thing to
die without seeing New York.

513
00:30:09,291 --> 00:30:10,364
And Jamie Darricott.

514
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:13,022
You will come back?

515
00:30:13,379 --> 00:30:14,280
Certainly not.

516
00:30:15,384 --> 00:30:17,319
For one thing. My trunks are packed.

517
00:30:17,832 --> 00:30:19,070
That's easy. Unpack them.

518
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:20,728
I can't. They are shipped.

519
00:30:21,052 --> 00:30:22,357
Easier still. But a dress.

520
00:30:23,164 --> 00:30:25,753
As a matter of fact, you should have a
new gown when you go out with me.

521
00:30:27,071 --> 00:30:28,115
You are impossible.

522
00:30:28,822 --> 00:30:30,345
Perhaps that's what makes me ..

523
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,012
Possible?

524
00:30:33,588 --> 00:30:34,804
Your aunt is approaching.

525
00:30:35,418 --> 00:30:37,890
You'd better not tell her of our plans.
She'll want to come along.

526
00:30:38,879 --> 00:30:41,426
What is the name of your hotel?
- The Holland Plaza.

527
00:30:41,814 --> 00:30:42,749
And your name?

528
00:30:43,805 --> 00:30:44,817
Norma Page.

529
00:30:45,667 --> 00:30:47,025
I will be there at 7:30.

530
00:30:49,121 --> 00:30:51,602
How do you do, Mrs Blanton.
- How do you do, Mr Darricott.

531
00:30:52,062 --> 00:30:55,095
Hello, aunt Theresa. I waited for you
and then Mr Darricott came along.

532
00:30:55,498 --> 00:30:57,314
That's the best thing
Mr Darricott has done.

533
00:30:58,304 --> 00:31:00,192
Women are always waiting for someone.

534
00:31:00,663 --> 00:31:04,084
And Mr Darricott comes along.
- Unfortunately, not always.

535
00:31:04,563 --> 00:31:05,927
I'm horribly late, Norma.

536
00:31:06,305 --> 00:31:08,549
I suppose I dare not allow
myself to believe that ..

537
00:31:08,938 --> 00:31:11,134
Fate arranged your lateness
for my special benefit?

538
00:31:11,488 --> 00:31:13,648
I am afraid not. It was the hairdresser.

539
00:31:14,088 --> 00:31:14,932
Come, Norma.

540
00:31:15,238 --> 00:31:17,169
Goodbye, Mr Darricott.
- Goodbye, Mrs Blanton.

541
00:31:18,362 --> 00:31:19,510
Au revoir, Miss Page.

542
00:31:20,296 --> 00:31:21,028
Goodbye.

543
00:31:31,793 --> 00:31:34,160
Mr James Darricott calling
for Miss Norma Page.

544
00:31:34,491 --> 00:31:38,153
I am sorry, sir. Miss Page checked out
of the hotel and left half an hour ago.

545
00:31:40,089 --> 00:31:41,132
You are quite sure?

546
00:31:41,426 --> 00:31:42,233
Yes, sir.

547
00:31:42,709 --> 00:31:44,416
She left this note for you, sir.

548
00:31:47,269 --> 00:31:48,056
Thank you.

549
00:31:52,688 --> 00:31:55,392
Mr Darricott. You didn't really believe
you could order me around, did you?

550
00:31:57,151 --> 00:32:00,069
I'm leaving for home as I told
you I would at seven-thirty.

551
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:03,220
Or is it goodbye? N.P.

552
00:32:17,928 --> 00:32:18,629
Gaston.

553
00:32:19,562 --> 00:32:21,280
Come on now.
You can do better than this.

554
00:32:47,041 --> 00:32:47,957
All aboard.

555
00:32:53,752 --> 00:32:55,278
Seeing someone off, Mr Darricott?

556
00:33:00,563 --> 00:33:02,336
Don't tell me you're
at a loss for words.

557
00:33:04,689 --> 00:33:06,105
I'm glad you came to see me off.

558
00:33:06,532 --> 00:33:09,178
If you hadn't, there's another train in
an hour and I would have taken it.

559
00:33:10,714 --> 00:33:11,329
Now.

560
00:33:11,907 --> 00:33:14,111
If you still want to show
me your New York.

561
00:33:16,642 --> 00:33:17,732
Now more than ever.

562
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:19,644
Well?

563
00:33:20,733 --> 00:33:21,402
Well.

564
00:33:22,718 --> 00:33:24,262
On your left we have the city hall.

565
00:33:27,638 --> 00:33:29,582
Is this an automobile or bedroom?

566
00:33:31,094 --> 00:33:32,032
It's a loan.

567
00:33:32,499 --> 00:33:33,384
From a lady?

568
00:33:34,372 --> 00:33:35,159
Naturally.

569
00:33:36,084 --> 00:33:38,217
I told the owner I had
to call on a sick aunt.

570
00:33:38,825 --> 00:33:40,171
And you are the sick aunt.

571
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:42,175
If you don't mind ..

572
00:33:42,392 --> 00:33:44,044
I'll dismiss it when we get to St Regis.

573
00:33:44,570 --> 00:33:45,442
Thanks a lot.

574
00:33:45,648 --> 00:33:47,529
A dirty old taxi that
everybody rides in ..

575
00:33:47,717 --> 00:33:50,925
Is so much nicer than some individual's
too-private car, don't you think?

576
00:33:51,901 --> 00:33:52,752
Or do you?

577
00:33:54,311 --> 00:33:55,095
I think.

578
00:34:01,351 --> 00:34:02,223
Hello, Jamie.

579
00:34:03,441 --> 00:34:04,559
Well, hello.

580
00:34:05,244 --> 00:34:06,304
How do you do.

581
00:34:06,784 --> 00:34:08,293
I am glad your aunt is better.

582
00:34:09,478 --> 00:34:10,643
Oh yes. Much.

583
00:34:11,630 --> 00:34:12,729
You are not alone?

584
00:34:13,147 --> 00:34:14,574
I'm waiting for Horace and Tony.

585
00:34:14,874 --> 00:34:16,565
We dine here and then go on to the play.

586
00:34:17,109 --> 00:34:18,127
Yes. That's nice.

587
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:20,546
You'll have a splendid evening.

588
00:34:20,734 --> 00:34:21,890
I am sure we shall.

589
00:34:22,848 --> 00:34:24,135
Remember me to your aunt.

590
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:25,271
Thanks.

591
00:34:26,914 --> 00:34:28,387
She wants to be remembered to you.

592
00:34:29,601 --> 00:34:32,386
Doesn't it embarrass you?
Meeting her here and dining with me?

593
00:34:33,437 --> 00:34:34,023
No.

594
00:34:34,404 --> 00:34:36,132
Well .. it embarrasses me.

595
00:34:37,898 --> 00:34:40,047
We'll go to the Aristide instead.
It's nicer anyway.

596
00:34:40,474 --> 00:34:42,748
There's been a shooting every
night there for the last month.

597
00:34:43,232 --> 00:34:44,567
Let's go this way.

598
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:47,024
I suppose Mrs Fendley
will hate you after this.

599
00:34:47,838 --> 00:34:49,496
No. She will merely hate you.

600
00:34:52,437 --> 00:34:53,543
Tell me about her.

601
00:34:54,528 --> 00:34:56,259
There's nothing to tell.
To her discredit.

602
00:34:56,857 --> 00:34:59,331
Which is all that would interest
another woman I imagine.

603
00:35:11,812 --> 00:35:13,879
How many cocktails have we had tonight?

604
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:16,740
I don't know. I gave up counting at six.

605
00:35:17,142 --> 00:35:19,265
Do you want to know why
you gave up counting at six?

606
00:35:21,638 --> 00:35:24,103
Alright. Why did I give
up counting at six?

607
00:35:25,258 --> 00:35:27,309
Because you cannot count over six.

608
00:35:27,713 --> 00:35:29,524
Hector. Number One for Mr Darricott.

609
00:35:30,915 --> 00:35:31,848
Who's that?

610
00:35:33,021 --> 00:35:33,920
It's Jamie.

611
00:35:37,739 --> 00:35:39,759
The town seems to be dripping
with Fendleys tonight.

612
00:35:55,051 --> 00:35:56,520
A sick aunt, huh?

613
00:35:57,789 --> 00:35:59,326
You dirty liar.

614
00:35:59,617 --> 00:36:01,251
Shush. You are a lady.

615
00:36:02,133 --> 00:36:04,269
Two tall glasses and some ice water.

616
00:36:06,957 --> 00:36:08,001
Won't you sit down?

617
00:36:08,225 --> 00:36:10,713
It's just as well you
didn't go with mother.

618
00:36:11,136 --> 00:36:12,638
Because dad would have sighted you.

619
00:36:13,076 --> 00:36:17,698
He's the only one in the whole town who
doesn't know of mother's frenzy for you.

620
00:36:19,021 --> 00:36:19,693
Jamie.

621
00:36:20,159 --> 00:36:21,755
If you and mother don't look out ..

622
00:36:22,140 --> 00:36:25,032
There will be the loudest
eruption since Vesuvius.

623
00:36:26,553 --> 00:36:28,500
Did you hear what I said about mother?

624
00:36:29,373 --> 00:36:30,789
Everyone has except the drummer.

625
00:36:32,701 --> 00:36:34,353
I want to extend to you.

626
00:36:35,067 --> 00:36:36,810
By a unanimous vote of thanks.

627
00:36:37,139 --> 00:36:39,026
For carrying Jamie off this evening.

628
00:36:40,247 --> 00:36:42,252
If you keep him from mother.

629
00:36:42,862 --> 00:36:44,748
I'll give you a pension for life.

630
00:36:45,470 --> 00:36:48,153
Then, when I want him I'll
just take him away from you.

631
00:36:49,314 --> 00:36:51,291
Could anything be fairer than that?

632
00:36:51,902 --> 00:36:53,017
Shall we dance?

633
00:36:54,190 --> 00:36:54,776
We?

634
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:56,852
I may.

635
00:36:57,514 --> 00:36:58,729
But we can't.

636
00:37:00,659 --> 00:37:02,929
Did you ever dance with Jamie, Miss ..?

637
00:37:03,631 --> 00:37:04,401
Miss ..?

638
00:37:04,933 --> 00:37:07,275
I hope you know your own name. I know.

639
00:37:08,083 --> 00:37:11,179
I am Miss Fendley if anybody
should happen to ask you. But ..

640
00:37:12,766 --> 00:37:13,843
Where was I?

641
00:37:18,348 --> 00:37:21,005
Mother doesn't approve
of me dancing with Jamie.

642
00:37:21,647 --> 00:37:23,490
She wants to have him all to herself.

643
00:37:25,716 --> 00:37:26,710
Rachel.

644
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:29,218
Will you do me a big favor?

645
00:37:29,690 --> 00:37:31,387
I'll do you any flavor, honey.

646
00:37:31,708 --> 00:37:32,842
Then go home.

647
00:37:33,526 --> 00:37:35,592
You're in no condition
for public appearances.

648
00:37:36,236 --> 00:37:38,630
Jamie, you do me a cruel injustice.

649
00:37:38,954 --> 00:37:39,884
Rachel, please.

650
00:37:40,429 --> 00:37:41,973
Sit back there where you belong.

651
00:37:42,161 --> 00:37:43,827
Well, I'd rather belong to you.

652
00:37:45,851 --> 00:37:47,905
I'm mad about you, if you want to know.

653
00:37:53,516 --> 00:37:54,446
Shall we dance?

654
00:38:18,023 --> 00:38:19,274
So I'll bet you a million.

655
00:38:20,016 --> 00:38:20,949
You're on.

656
00:38:22,757 --> 00:38:24,720
Nope. I have changed my mind.

657
00:38:26,375 --> 00:38:28,544
You're trying to take advantage of me.

658
00:38:35,719 --> 00:38:36,442
Jamie.

659
00:38:36,705 --> 00:38:37,456
Jamie.

660
00:38:37,982 --> 00:38:40,708
Jamie. Peyton Walden here bets
me a million I'll marry him.

661
00:38:41,094 --> 00:38:42,878
I'll bet him a million
he don't marry me.

662
00:38:43,325 --> 00:38:46,442
Come on, Mr Walden.
Put your million in Jamie's hands.

663
00:38:48,557 --> 00:38:49,543
Very likely.

664
00:38:50,604 --> 00:38:52,779
Oh, very likely.
- Put up or shut up.

665
00:38:53,333 --> 00:38:54,567
Where is your million?

666
00:38:54,889 --> 00:38:55,850
Where's yours?

667
00:38:56,038 --> 00:38:57,903
I don't have to have
mine because you lose.

668
00:38:58,427 --> 00:38:59,685
You answered me already.

669
00:39:00,187 --> 00:39:01,707
How do you make that out?

670
00:39:02,084 --> 00:39:04,131
You bet me a million
that you'd marry me.

671
00:39:04,626 --> 00:39:07,775
I am the one to decide.
I decide you don't marry me.

672
00:39:08,207 --> 00:39:10,250
I bet you another million I do.

673
00:39:11,948 --> 00:39:13,442
I'll take that back too.

674
00:39:13,844 --> 00:39:15,146
Alright. Where's your money?

675
00:39:15,468 --> 00:39:18,914
Pay me the million you owe on the first
bet and I'll put it up for the second.

676
00:39:19,577 --> 00:39:21,417
I don't owe you.
- See?

677
00:39:22,293 --> 00:39:23,309
You are a welsher.

678
00:39:23,894 --> 00:39:26,232
Do you imagine I would marry a welsher?

679
00:39:27,152 --> 00:39:28,829
You will marry me.
- Never.

680
00:39:29,142 --> 00:39:31,086
Never, never speak to me again.
Do you hear?

681
00:39:32,159 --> 00:39:33,746
Miss whoosis ..

682
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:36,369
Would you marry a welsher?

683
00:39:37,045 --> 00:39:38,081
Who cares?

684
00:39:38,379 --> 00:39:39,876
I'm going to make a riot with you.

685
00:39:40,958 --> 00:39:42,400
Rachel.
- What do you want?

686
00:39:43,141 --> 00:39:44,160
Now listen to me.

687
00:39:44,895 --> 00:39:47,163
I want you to get Peyton out
of here and take him home.

688
00:39:47,859 --> 00:39:49,496
You don't want to make a riot with him.

689
00:39:49,783 --> 00:39:51,636
He'll bite himself and
die of hydrophobia.

690
00:39:52,084 --> 00:39:53,255
I'm going home myself.

691
00:39:53,734 --> 00:39:55,658
You want me to get old Peyton home?

692
00:39:56,291 --> 00:39:58,545
That's it exactly.
Miss Page and I are leaving.

693
00:39:59,568 --> 00:40:00,408
I got it.

694
00:40:01,704 --> 00:40:02,509
I got it.

695
00:40:03,719 --> 00:40:06,359
I'll get old Peyton home.
Never mind, I'll handle him.

696
00:40:07,275 --> 00:40:08,007
Peyton.

697
00:40:08,577 --> 00:40:10,540
Peyton, old boy, old boy, old boy.

698
00:40:11,278 --> 00:40:12,007
Come on.

699
00:40:12,461 --> 00:40:13,194
Go home.

700
00:40:19,579 --> 00:40:21,836
I never knew it could get to
five in the morning so quickly.

701
00:40:22,024 --> 00:40:23,955
I never knew it could get
to five in the morning.

702
00:40:24,899 --> 00:40:25,779
Where to now?

703
00:40:26,042 --> 00:40:27,401
To my hotel if you don't mind.

704
00:40:28,988 --> 00:40:30,048
What is the matter?

705
00:40:30,236 --> 00:40:32,514
Am I a kill-sport by going home
in the middle of the evening?

706
00:40:32,702 --> 00:40:35,168
Why, you haven't even seen the
skyline from my apartment yet.

707
00:40:35,741 --> 00:40:36,862
Mr Darricott.

708
00:40:38,092 --> 00:40:40,820
You don't mean you are asking me to
your apartment to see your ship models?

709
00:40:41,384 --> 00:40:43,970
Or is it your collection of
real old English bindings?

710
00:40:44,405 --> 00:40:46,154
I haven't read a novel for months, so ..

711
00:40:46,473 --> 00:40:48,026
I'm not quite sure what the ruse is.

712
00:40:48,918 --> 00:40:51,199
When I invite you to my
apartment to see the skyline.

713
00:40:51,702 --> 00:40:54,179
I invite you to my apartment to
see the skyline and that's all.

714
00:40:55,014 --> 00:40:56,516
Maybe that's why I am disappointed.

715
00:40:56,874 --> 00:40:59,055
It's really the most beautiful
sight in the whole city.

716
00:40:59,243 --> 00:41:01,603
Particularly at this hour with
dawn just breaking over the town.

717
00:41:02,310 --> 00:41:04,363
Skyscrapers like so many jagged peaks.

718
00:41:05,113 --> 00:41:05,957
The streets.

719
00:41:06,235 --> 00:41:07,426
Like so many canyons.

720
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:09,729
Alright.

721
00:41:10,254 --> 00:41:11,041
I'll come.

722
00:41:13,212 --> 00:41:13,856
Taxi.

723
00:41:18,624 --> 00:41:19,239
Sir.

724
00:41:19,974 --> 00:41:21,668
I am sorry, Mr Darricott.

725
00:41:22,087 --> 00:41:22,936
I tried.

726
00:41:23,981 --> 00:41:25,025
I don't understand.

727
00:41:25,441 --> 00:41:26,542
I think I understand.

728
00:41:27,357 --> 00:41:28,185
What is it?

729
00:41:28,456 --> 00:41:31,048
Miss Fendley, sir. Miss Rachel Fendley.

730
00:41:31,688 --> 00:41:32,274
Oh.

731
00:41:32,938 --> 00:41:33,896
Alright, Eugene.

732
00:41:37,272 --> 00:41:39,505
I should hate to interfere with
any of your engagements.

733
00:41:41,299 --> 00:41:42,372
Please don't go now.

734
00:41:42,833 --> 00:41:43,934
I may need your help.

735
00:42:00,287 --> 00:42:00,959
Hello.

736
00:42:02,287 --> 00:42:04,593
I got rid of Peyton as you told me.

737
00:42:05,367 --> 00:42:06,268
And here I am.

738
00:42:10,083 --> 00:42:11,499
I told you to get rid of Peyton?

739
00:42:15,616 --> 00:42:16,889
Who are you trying to fool?

740
00:42:17,286 --> 00:42:18,330
Yourself or Miss ..

741
00:42:18,942 --> 00:42:20,338
Miss whatshername there?

742
00:42:23,354 --> 00:42:24,814
I am awful tired.

743
00:42:26,129 --> 00:42:27,402
Yes. I can understand that.

744
00:42:28,924 --> 00:42:31,544
You've got to go home.
- No. I don't want to go home.

745
00:42:31,939 --> 00:42:34,461
She cannot go home in this condition.
Why not put her to bed here?

746
00:42:34,842 --> 00:42:36,245
No. I don't want to go to bed.

747
00:42:36,433 --> 00:42:38,507
You want me to help you?
- I don't know what I want.

748
00:42:38,814 --> 00:42:40,572
What you want most right now is sleep.

749
00:42:41,552 --> 00:42:42,224
Jamie.

750
00:42:42,701 --> 00:42:44,317
Come on, child. Put your arm around me.

751
00:42:45,514 --> 00:42:46,959
There is a bedroom just in there.

752
00:42:49,493 --> 00:42:50,909
You'll find everything you need.

753
00:42:51,176 --> 00:42:52,505
We women must stick together.

754
00:42:52,693 --> 00:42:54,537
No. I don't want to stick together.

755
00:42:59,692 --> 00:43:01,079
There you are. Right over here.

756
00:43:01,875 --> 00:43:02,670
Jamie.

757
00:43:07,523 --> 00:43:09,335
Listen, darling. Over here. Come on.
- No.

758
00:43:09,748 --> 00:43:11,078
Let me help you.
- No.

759
00:43:12,171 --> 00:43:13,911
I don't want to go home.

760
00:43:14,522 --> 00:43:15,657
No. Me do it.

761
00:43:17,737 --> 00:43:18,323
No.

762
00:43:19,277 --> 00:43:20,000
Jamie.

763
00:43:20,757 --> 00:43:21,429
Jamie.

764
00:43:25,112 --> 00:43:25,794
Jamie.

765
00:43:29,719 --> 00:43:31,554
I'll have coffee ready
in a few moments, sir.

766
00:43:31,742 --> 00:43:32,385
Good.

767
00:43:33,128 --> 00:43:33,800
And ..

768
00:43:35,462 --> 00:43:38,072
Tell the operator downstairs
that I am not in to anyone.

769
00:43:38,499 --> 00:43:39,429
Very good, sir.

770
00:43:52,606 --> 00:43:54,897
I couldn't get her in the
tub but she's asleep now.

771
00:43:56,027 --> 00:43:57,786
There was a picture in
there of her mother.

772
00:43:58,251 --> 00:43:59,696
It seemed to bother her a little.

773
00:44:01,998 --> 00:44:03,463
A nice little civilization.

